RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRANCIPANTS raced off the rail, off the pace, advanced on the turn, bid three wide at the quarter pole, rallied outside in the lane, closed steadily in the final furlong and was along late for the win. APOLLO U ANYWHERE set the pace on the inside, responded when roused at the top of the lane, dug in gamely on the rail and yielded grudgingly. COOKIN ROSES broke outward, stalked close up two wide, bid onthe turn, dug in between rivals in the stretch drive and then weakened. RANK AND FILE tracked along the inside, chased inside on the turn, lacked a winning bid and finished evenly. FANCY EMPRESS was outrun early and did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference by condition eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLAME SHIFTER vied inside for the lead, dropped back a bit entering the far turn, chased, came again outside of MINNESOTA MOON in the stretch run, dug in gamely, wore down that rival in deep stretch and prevailed. MINNESOTA MOON drifted in some in front of rivals nearing the first turn, then vied two wide for command, shook free entering the far turn, drew clear, dug in gamely inside in the final furlong and yielded grudgingly late. ICE AXE was off a bit slow, tracked on the inside, chased inside on the far turn, rallied mildly in the lane and bested the others. GOING AT IT steadied nearing the first turn, settled off the rail, off the pace, went three wide on the far turn, moved to the rail in the stretch and failed to threaten. GOLD SMOKE steadied entering the clubhouse turn, then pulled in the early stages, dropped back on the far turn, came wide into the stretch and passed tired ones. ARMAVIR stalked two wide, chased on the far turn and gave way. BORDER SPIN steadied nearing the clubhouse turn, went four wide into the turn, then raced off the pace inside and gave way. A Jockey's Objection by the rider of BORDER SPIN against MINNESOTA MOON was dismissed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 94. Allowance Purse 31500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since April 18 Allowed 2 lbs. (Cla iming races for $20,000 or less not considered in estimating allowances) (Preference by condition eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PAPA ROCKET was off slowly, outrun early, advanced on the turn, came wide into the stretch, rallied outside, closed willingly in deep stretch, surged and gamely prevailed at the wire. WEST WARPATH settled off the pace, stalked two wide on the turn, bumped with TWIRLING ROSES entering the stretch, rallied between rivals, surged late and just missed. SONNYISNOTSOFUNNY was bumped and off a bit slow, raced off the rail, off the pace, rallied beteen rivals in the stretch, was bumped soundly at the eighth pole, continued to rally, steadied lacking room at the sixteenth marker, then closed outside and got third. TEE BURNS dueled inside for the lead, shook free coming to the quarter pole, dug in gamely in the stretch run and weakened late. TWIRLING ROSES chased inside, moved up on the rail on the turn, then was in tight and bumped entering the stretch, steadied, then rallied on the rail and lacked room late forced to check sharply. FOLLOW THE SIGNS raced off the pace inside, swung wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. WINGING WAYS was bumped at the start, dueled two wide for the lead, then chased and faded. After a Stewards' Inquiry along with Jockey Objections by the rider of TWIRLING ROSES against TEE BURNS and WEST WARPATH, the race was declared official.
